    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-26T01:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-26T01:35:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/1186: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-26T10:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 26, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 26—9:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>457. Faced with responsibility of taking steps with possible grave repercussions,
                    Iranian economy [<hi rend="italic">Government?</hi>] is showing itself reluctant
                    to take steps that will force the departure of Millspaugh and his mission.
                    Legation has been informed that at secret session yesterday majority of better
                    elements of Majlis felt Millspaugh should stay under a system whereby a council
                    of Iranians would review his economic regulations before promulgation.
                    Millspaugh is to appear before Majlis today in secret session to discuss this
                    idea and it now appears possible that a <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> may
                    be worked out which will permit Millspaugh to remain. Should this occur, it is
                    difficult to see how Saed government could remain in office and still enjoy the
                    confidence of the Majlis and the people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
